$interpreted: : Three days later...
Financial Officer: The schedule is already far too tight! If we add even more to the schedule, the workers will not be able to handle the workload!
Douglas: Then increase the pay! Everything has a price and we will pay that damn price no matter what!
Financial Officer: The kingdom's finances can't sustain this kind of spending!
Douglas: Then increase taxes!
Jahan: Your Majesty Regent Theodore, Jahan here to report something important.
Theodore: Speak.
Jahan: Jahan was interrogating the assassin with Sir Dylan. However, during the interrogation, said assassin blurted out something quite offensive...
Jahan: Those words can almost be considered high treason.  Your Majesty must know about this!
Jahan: The wings of the Half-Blood... shall swipe away the imposter blocking the Sun.
Theodore: ......
Jahan: Your Majesty, as soon as Jahan heard this, I immediately came to report in fear that it might damage your reputation.
Jahan: Do you want Jahan to handle this for you?
Theodore: Who else knows about this?
Jahan: No worries your Majesty. Besides Sir Dylan, only I know about it.
Jahan: M... My sincere gratitude your Majesty. Are you doing this because you realize Jahan's lack of training and... decide to train Jahan yourself? But...
Jahan: Jahan... might be unable to take it. If it dirties your precious hands...
Theodore: What do you want to say?
Jahan: Cough... Dirty things, are suitable for those who don't care about the dirt. That way, your Majesty's hands can be kept squeaky clean...
Jahan: C... Cough. Thank you, your Majesty...
Theodore: That nonsense the assassin spewed, I don't want a third person besides the two of us to know about it.
Jahan: Your Majesty, do you mean that you want Sir Dylan...
Theodore: Think about it yourself. If you still value your life, you had better prove your worth to me.
